o 180°C.","Prick pastry base with a fork to prevent air bubbles. Line pastry base with baking paper and fill with pie weights, rice or dried beans. Place tart tin onto a baking tray and bake for 10 minutes (180°C)."," Remove pie weights, rice or dried beans and baking paper. Bake for a further 5-10 minutes (180°C) or until pastry is light golden. Set aside to cool. Reduce oven temperature to 160°C.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add all remaining ingredients, including 250 g of the reserved ricotta and mix <b>5 sec\/\/speed 5<b>.","Transfer ricotta mixture into pastry case and smooth surface with the back of a spoon. Bake for 30-40 minutes (160°C), or until filling is just set. Turn off oven and leave cheesecake to cool in oven with door ajar for 40 minutes. Remove from oven and leave to cool completely. Cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for a minimum 2 hours or until ready to serve.","Remove star anise, cinnamon quill and vanilla bean pod from syrup and discard. Place cheesecake onto serving platter and drizzle with soaked figs and syrup before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Botrytis soaked figs","content":["150 g botrytis semillon","70 g caster sugar","1 vanilla bean, cut into half lengthways, seeds scraped","1 cinnamon quill","2 star anise","2 pinches ground nutmeg","150 g dried figs"]},{"title":"Ricotta","content":["1800 g full cream milk","80 g white vinegar"]},{"title":"Shortcrust pastry","content":["100 g unsalted butter, chilled and cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing","230 g plain flour","1 pinch salt","50 g icing sugar","3 egg yolks"]},{"title":"Cheesecake filling","content":["80 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa), broken into pieces","40 g raw hazelnuts, toasted","150 g cream cheese","100 g caster sugar","100 g sour cream","2 eggs","40 g mixed peel","40 g brandy"]}],"id":"r97489","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-HE0nkaGRkyQ\/XZWpty6RgzI\/AAAAAAAAfN8\/8XJqCjz-P88Ofk0AGzY4SAeK4QoZFIEwgC